         </physdescstructured>
         <physdesc localtype="container_summary">(6 boxes)</physdesc>
         <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">1931-1959</unitdate>
         <abstract id="aspace_541158927dfade8ad61af19f06c35052">The materials consist of photographs documenting the construction of Sterling Divinity Quadrangle at Yale. Also included are interior and exterior views.</abstract>
    
      </did>
      <odd id="aspace_a6a0b7ceae3ebf54ddb8af40a6b0a0cb">
         <head>General note</head>
         <p>Forms part of Yale Record Group 46-B (YRG 46-B), Records and materials documenting individual Yale buildings, facilities, and grounds.</p>  
      </odd>
      <prefercite id="aspace_43dfc5245937c503668e22e7089f0567">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Sterling Divinity Quadrangle, Yale University, Photographs (RU 628). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_3d107ff852628299b74eae9c59a2fccb">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <arrangement id="aspace_804a88e04d6f84979f49c786d1c0175d">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The materials are arranged in four series: I. Construction progress photographs, 1931-1957. II. General views, 1931-1959. III. Slides and transparencies. IV. Folio.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_26cc63fd1001e156ad61bd5367fd3657">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The materials consist of photographs documenting the construction of Sterling Divinity Quadrangle at Yale. Also included are interior and exterior views.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
